/**
 * Enumeration of the medical service types available in the emergency dispatch system.
 *
 * <p>Each constant represents a distinct medical specialty that a hospital may offer.
 * This enumeration is used both to characterise the capabilities of a {@link Hospital}
 * and to express the care requirement of a {@link Patient}, enabling the
 * {@link AssignmentService} to match patients with compatible hospitals.</p>
 *
 * @author Maissa Tirsane, Anas Chokri, Iyed Souissi, Valery Vo-Van
 * @version 1.0
 */
public enum HospitalServiceType {
    /** General medicine, accepted by all hospitals as a baseline service. */
    GENERAL,
    /** Neurological care, required for conditions such as stroke or epilepsy. */
    NEUROLOGY,
    /** Cardiac care, required for conditions such as myocardial infarction. */
    CARDIOLOGY,
    /** Paediatric care, required for patients under the age of majority. */
    PEDIATRICS
}
